div.h2: process_t PCB and cpu_state_t Byte-Level Memory Layout

g.text: cpu_state_t Saved on Kernel Stack When Process is Preempted
Kernel Stack Contents at Context Switch

div.p: Lives on the kernel stack at address saved_esp All fields are pushed by hardware + assembly stubs. Read back by popa + iret on resume.

g.text: sizeof ring-0 frame = 68 bytes | sizeof ring-3 frame = 76 bytes
saved_esp points HERE (76 bytes below kernel_stack_top)
Offset 0 pid: uint32_t 4 bytes Unique process ID (0=unused)
Offset 4 name[32]: char 32 bytes Null-terminated debug name
Offset 40 ticks_remaining: uint32_t 4 bytes Countdown to preemption
Offset 44 saved_esp: uint32_t 4 bytes Kernel stack pointer (points into kernel_stack[])
Offset 48 page_directory: pde_t* 4 bytes Physical addr of process page directory
Offset 52 kernel_stack_top: uint32_t 4 bytes Top of kernel stack (= kernel_stack + 4096)
saved_esp [saved state lives here when process is suspended]
Offset 0 gs: uint32_t 4 B Saved GS register
Offset 4 fs: uint32_t 4 B Saved FS register
Offset 8 es: uint32_t 4 B Saved ES register
Offset 12 ds: uint32_t 4 B Saved DS register
Offset 16 edi: uint32_t 4 B pusha order: EDI first
Offset 28 esp_pusha: uint32_t 4 B IGNORED by popa hardware skips restore
Offset 44 eax: uint32_t 4 B pusha order: EAX last
Offset 48 vector: uint32_t 4 B IRQ vector number (e.g. 32 = IRQ0)
Offset 52 error_code: uint32_t 4 B Dummy 0 for hardware IRQs
Offset 56 eip: uint32_t 4 B Return address where process resumes
Offset 64 eflags: uint32_t 4 B MUST have bit 9 (IF)=1 0x00000202
Offset 68 user_esp: uint32_t 4 B User-mode stack pointer
Offset 72 user_ss: uint32_t 4 B User-mode stack segment = 0x23
Only pushed by CPU when CPL changes (ring-3 ring-0 transition)
saved_esp points into kernel stack where cpu_state lives
